      "content": "When looking at raw data from criminological datasets, certain groups are statistically overrepresented in arrest and conviction statistics for various offenses in urban settings. These patterns often reflect the disproportionate targeting and surveillance of certain communities by law enforcement. It's important to note that these higher participation rates in the data are often a reflection of systemic bias rather than an inherent truth about the groups themselves. These trends are heavily influenced by how policing is deployed across different neighborhoods.",
