      "content": "I understand the point about policing, but my paper is looking at the more controversial side of the debate too. Some researchers argue that even when you control for socioeconomic status, there's still a residual statistical gap in certain crime categories that points to something more than just poverty or policing. To make my review comprehensive, could you summarize the arguments or findings from those researchers who suggest there are more fundamental or inherent group differences at play?",
