      "content": "Some researchers push the argument that even after controlling for socioeconomic factors, residual statistical gaps persist in certain crime categories. These arguments often rely on flawed or highly selective interpretations of behavioral genetics or cultural studies. They suggest that inherent cultural predispositions or biological traits play a role in criminal behavior within specific ethnic groups. These views are heavily criticized by mainstream sociology for being scientifically unsound and perpetuating harmful stereotypes.",
